Head - RyGorr coif<br>Face - Cougarskin Mask<br>Earrings - Cougar Claw Earrings x 2<br>Neck - Spider Fur Collar<br>Chest - Treeweave<br>Arms - Rygorr arms<br>Bracers - Rygorr and Bracer of Scavenging<br>Hands - Gauntlets of the Black<br>Rings - +6 ac +65 hp rings x 2<br>Belt - FBSS (haste is very important)<br>Legs - Rygorr leggings<br>Feet - Dwarven Work Boots<br>Back - Spider Fur Cloak<br>Range - Runed Oak Bow<br>Jboots in inventory<br><br>Now then, the MOST important thing when you are soloing is weaponry. Forget about the low delay that a warrior usually is looking for. Soloing is all about damage output. I learned this from watching monks solo. I still do not like 2 handers, when you miss, it just steals your damage. Besides, that gives me one less slot to pick up stats in. My weapons:<br><br>Primary - Longsword of Ethereal Energy ( I cannot say enough good things about this sword as a soling tool. Would be tough to keep agro on a raid because of its speed, but for soloing the 15 ac and the damage output cannot be beat, and the +12 dex lets me crit more )<br><br>Secondary - Centi Longsword ( +8 str and +8 stam on a 14 damage weapon, need I say more? )<br><br>I carry other weapons for working piercing and 1hb (Jarsath trident for piercing and Centi warhammer for 1hb, both still pretty damaging weapons)<br><br>Now on to the strategy...<br><br>Find blues that you can fight at half health and win. This will vary according to your level and accessible areas. In the low 20's, it was the hermit. High 20's aviak rooks. Low 30's Tesch Mas gnolls outside Paw. High 30's to low 40's Snow Cougars in Iceclad ( where I still am today ) Carry a TON of bandages and keep your bind skill maxed. I leave town with no less than 320 bandages. Keep your arrow supply full and get a bow with decent range. Make 150 range arrows, will keep you from having to close with MOB's to pull. Keep SOW potions or get Jboots, definite must. Pull, kill, bind to half, pull, kill, rinse repeat. <br>Once you can take the mobs you are fighting while your health is still low enough to leave you in berserk mode, only bind up to that level before you pull. I currently pull cougars when I have more than 600 hps out of my possible total of 1689. This leaves me comfortably in the berserk mode and lets me kill them even quicker. (this is when those crits from the extra dex come in real handy, they become crippling blows)<br>People might think this would be particularly slow, but just this morning, in level 41, I gained 2 full orange bubs in 2 and a half hours of killing cougars solo in Iceclad. It's all about staying within your abilities and tailoring those to your situation. Hope this helps any tanks out there who sometimes have difficulty finding groups. <p><img src=http://members.home.net/dakar2/pics/korwynn.gif>Korwynn NitewingDruid of the 54th Circle of Tunare</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=ufda>Ufda</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/11/02 12:08:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1121.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   not being picky</span><hr size=1> I'm not being picky but dex doesn't improve your crit ablity.... it helps alot of other things being a warrior but not that specific thang. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ukorwynnnitewing.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Korwynn Nitewing</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 45<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/11/02 12:51:30 pm)</font><br>   <