 exp group with no dex buffs, then go to a raid or a really good group where the shammy gives you +200 dex.  I crit much more often when i have higher dex.  I KNOW it affects proc, because when I am using my Blood Point with no dex buffs, It might proc like 2 or 3 times in a fight.  But when I am buffed above 200 dex, I start proccing like 5-7 times in one fight, very nice.   <p><a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=35162">Khallim Bloodhelm</a><BR>Dwarven Mercenary of the 53rd War <BR>~Nobody tosses a Dwarf!~</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uxendrix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xendrix</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/14/02 2:27:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1121.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Warrior soloing</span><hr size=1> I can gaurantee that dex effects both crits and procs.  I have a naturally lame dex to begin with.  Add in the negatives from my blood runed greaves I am well below 80, and it is almost embarassing.  When not buffed, I rarely if ever get procs from my bandage dagger, club of the ice ocean,etc and I rarely see critical hits.  Buff my dex to 120+, and all of a sudden the procs and crits start flying by left and right.  I think once you are nearing the cap, you are going to notice much less of a difference, but if you have a low dex to begin with, as in below 100, and then crank it up, you will notice a significant difference in procs/crits.<br><br>-Galdaen<br>Sun Clan of Warriors<br>Solusek Ro<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=